<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Following the new ICN, 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia smallii" order="Pucciniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="smallii">Hemileia smallii</taxonomicName>
has priority even though the type specimen includes only the asexual stage of this species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Fernier, H" journalOrPublisher="Revue de mycolgie, Paris" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="58 - 63" title="Contribution a l'etude d'une Rouille de Strophanthus sarmentosus due a Hemileia smallii Wakef. et Hansford." volume="19" year="1954">Fernier (1954)</bibRefCitation>
described a name for the teleomorph using a different type specimen. Because he used the same epithet, that name is an illegitimate, later homonym. For this reason 
<bibRefCitation pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Gjaerum et al. (2000)</bibRefCitation>
established another name for this species based on a different type specimen that is here regarded as a taxonomic synonym.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
